snippet.textDisplay:
Coke Studio is all about 'combining and fusing' different musicians and their styles to make a new product and that's the idea about it. How can you imagine or even expect a student (Rahat Fateh Ali Khan) to match the flawlessness of his teacher/mentor Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan? This is just like expecting Yasir Shah to bowl like Wasim Akram Live, guys. The idea is to mix different music styles into 'twist and turn' into something new so let's appreciate creativity, music and innovation. It's sad to see how everybody is whining that the song didn't match NFAK's class. It can never. The covers cannot match the class, no matter how much you can. Not only in Pakistan but even in international. Over more than 88,000 covers have been done of Beat It by Michael Jackson but the original stays original and irreplaceable. No matter how much of a badass 'moonwalker' you might be, but can you do it better than Michael Jackson? No you can't. He was the master of it and it is just something that he can do it in the most flawless manner. So let's stop being naive and shallow, let's appreciate the madness. Coke Studio is NOT about giving tributes and doing justice to iconic songs, people. It's about fusing two or three different artists and making a unified product with their own respectable styles. You won't get Naseebo Lal with the rock n' roll-y Umair Jaswal anywhere but here. This is the entire idea of this show. Enjoy the music!

PS: You 'kill' the creative process when you start comparing them. You just cannot measure it so just try listening to it as if it's a new thing to you and you will learn appreciating what they tried doing with it.
